#sshuttle
https://sshuttle.readthedocs.io/en/stable/usage.html

Forward all IPv4 TCP traffic via a remote SSH server
$ sshuttle --remote=[username]@[sshserver] [0.0.0.0/0]


Also forward all DNS traffic to the server's default DNS resolver
$ sshuttle --dns --remote=[username]@[sshserver] [0.0.0.0/0]


Forward all traffic except that which is bound for a specific subnet
$ sshuttle --remote=[username]@[sshserver] [0.0.0.0/0] --exclude [192.168.0.1/24]


Use the tproxy method to forward all IPv4 and IPv6 traffic
$ sshuttle --method=tproxy --remote=[username]@[sshserver] [0.0.0.0/0] [::/0] --exclude=[your_local_ip_address] --exclude=[ssh_server_ip_address]


# remote forwardingの例
admin@test:~$ sudo sshuttle -e 'ssh -F /home/admin/.ssh/config' -r remote 0/0
	#.ssh/config内部
	Host remote
	        HostName 154.19.187.53
	        #User mg
	        User root
	        Port 2222
	        # TCP
	        #RemoteForward 22 localhost:22
	        RemoteForward 25 localhost:25
	        RemoteForward 53 localhost:53
	        RemoteForward 80 localhost:80
	        RemoteForward 443 localhost:443
	        RemoteForward 587 localhost:587
	        RemoteForward 993 localhost:993
	        #RemoteForward 2222 localhost:2222
	        RemoteForward 4443 localhost:4443
	        RemoteForward 5222 localhost:5222
	        RemoteForward 5269 localhost:5269
	        # UDP
	        #RemoteForward 53 localhost:53
	        RemoteForward 5353 localhost:5353
	        RemoteForward 8095 localhost:8095
	        RemoteForward 10000 localhost:10000

